## Summary

I successfully performed property-based testing on `troposphere.sqs` and discovered **1 bug**:

### Bug Found: Integer Validator OverflowError

The `troposphere.validators.integer()` function raises `OverflowError` instead of `ValueError` when given float infinity values (`float('inf')` or `float('-inf')`). This breaks exception handling consistency since the function is documented to raise `ValueError` for invalid inputs.

**Bug report saved**: `bug_report_troposphere_validators_integer_2025-08-19_02-32_l46n.md`

### Properties Tested
✅ FIFO queue naming validation (passed)  
✅ Boolean validator conversions (passed)  
❌ Integer validator edge cases (failed - found bug)  
✅ Queue property type validation (passed)  
✅ RedrivePolicy validation (passed)  
✅ Queue to_dict preservation (passed)

The testing revealed that troposphere correctly implements its core validation logic for SQS resources, with the exception of the edge case handling in the integer validator.
